%N A395240 Table read by falling antidiagonals: T(n,k) is the number of k-colorings of the faces of a n-bipyramid up to prismatic symmetry. n >= 3, k >= 0.
%C A395240 Colorings are counted up to prismatic symmetry of order 4n.
%H A395240 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bipyramid">Bipyramid</a>.
%H A395240 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dihedral_symmetry_in_three_dimensions">Dihedral symmetry in three dimensions</a>.
%F A395240 T(n,k) = A396913(n,k) = A321791(2*n,k) if n is odd.
%F A395240 T(2,k) = A222187(k).
